cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on language acquisition and generalization in a virtual environment. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper involves building a virtual agent that learns language and takes actions to receive rewards. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the agent learns simultaneously the visual representations of the world, the language, and the action control. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the agent sees images of the surrounding environment. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves a virtual agent navigating a 2D maze-like world.
